2. **Cryptographic API Key Validation**:
```java
public class ApiKeyValidator {
    private final SecretVaultClient vault;

    public boolean isValid(String apiKey) {
        // Keys are hashed in storage - never stored plaintext
        String keyHash = sha256(apiKey);
        ApiKeyRecord record = vault.getApiKeyRecord(keyHash);

        if (record == null) return false;
        if (record.isRevoked()) return false;
        if (record.getExpiresAt().isBefore(Instant.now())) return false;

        return true;
    }

    private String sha256(String input) {
        MessageDigest digest = MessageDigest.getInstance("SHA-256");
        byte[] hash = digest.digest(input.getBytes());
        return Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(hash);
    }
}
```

3. **Mutual TLS for Service-to-Service**:
```java
public class ServiceAuthenticator {
    public boolean verifyMtls(HttpServletRequest request) {
        X509Certificate[] certs = (X509Certificate[]) 
            request.getAttribute("javax.servlet.request.X509Certificate");

        if (certs == null || certs.length == 0) {
            return false;
        }

        X509Certificate clientCert = certs[0];

        // Verify certificate is from trusted CA
        if (!isTrustedCa(clientCert.getIssuerDN())) {
            return false;
        }

        // Verify certificate is not revoked (check CRL or OCSP)
        if (isCertificateRevoked(clientCert)) {
            return false;
        }

        // Verify service identity from certificate CN/SAN
        String serviceIdentity = extractServiceIdentity(clientCert);
        return isAuthorizedService(serviceIdentity);
    }
}
